      "note": "Mubin: perspicuous. The reason why I have not used a simpler word, such as \"plain\" or \"clear\" is explained in n. 716 to 5:15. Al Mustafa's sermons were not polite reminders, with an eye to the flattery of weaknesses in high places or national vanities or crowd passions. They brought out every foible into the glare of light, by a fiery eloquence fed by inspiration from Allah (Cf. 38:70)."
